# SkySlope Forms PDF analysis (single standard)

There is **one** analysis path for every PDF the scripts open. No conditional “only OCR if thin” logic.

## Pipeline (every page in the read window)

Module: `scripts/skyslope-pdf-insight.mjs`

1. **pdf.js (legacy build)** — `getTextContent` and `getAnnotations` per page (widgets, links, etc.).
2. **Mandatory OCR on every page** the script reads (same count as the text pass), except when **`SKYSLOPE_PDF_OCR_MAX_PAGES`** or the programmatic **`ocrMaxPages`** option (used by log/workbook/audit scripts) caps the OCR engine below the read depth. Those tail pages still get the dual layout; the OCR section states the cap in plain language (no silent skip).
3. **Fixed page layout** — each page string is always:

   - `<<< Page N >>>`
   - `--- MACHINE TEXT LAYER (pdf.js extractText) ---` …
   - `--- RENDERED IMAGE OCR (mandatory same-page pass) ---` …

   So machine text and image-derived text are **never** ambiguously merged without labels.

4. **OCR engines** (per page, first nonempty result): **Poppler `pdftoppm` + Tesseract CLI**; else **`tesseract.js`** on a **pdf.js + `@napi-rs/canvas`** render.

5. **Downstream** — sale agreement extraction, e-sign heuristics, and Flags use the **full dual string** so OCR and text layer both contribute.

## Environment knobs

| Variable | Role |
|----------|------|
| `SKYSLOPE_PDF_MAX_PAGES` | Max pages read per PDF (text + OCR layout for each). |
| `SKYSLOPE_PDF_OCR_MAX_PAGES` | Optional cap on how many pages run the **OCR engine**; default equals pages read. Lower values label skipped tail pages in the OCR block. |
| `SKYSLOPE_LOG_PDF_MAX_PAGES` | Comprehensive log: max pages per PDF for both text read and OCR (default 2). |
| `SKYSLOPE_WORKBOOK_PDF_MAX_PAGES` | Transaction workbook `PDF_sample`: max pages per PDF when `SKYSLOPE_WORKBOOK_PDF_SAMPLE=1` (default 8). |
| `SKYSLOPE_AUDIT_PDF_MAX_PAGES` | Master folder audit: max pages per prioritized PDF (default 12). |
| `SKYSLOPE_PDF_OCR_DPI` | Render resolution for the tesseract.js path (default 200, clamped 144 to 300). |
| `SKYSLOPE_BRIEF_MAX_PDFS` | Brief only: how many files get this pipeline. |
| `SKYSLOPE_MAX_PDF_BYTES` | Download size cap. |

## What this does not replace

Principal Broker execution judgment and line-by-line review in SkySlope.

## Agent behavior

Extend **`skyslope-pdf-insight.mjs`** only when changing the standard. Do not fork parallel PDF logic inside one-off scripts.
